title.narrative: Output 3.4: Protection – Service Access & Quality“Service providers in targeted locations have strengthened capacities to prevent violence against children and deliver quality child protection interventions to children at risk, including those in contact with law, on the move and survivors of violence.

description.narrative: The institutionalization of Case Management functions enabled support to nearly 29,000 children during 2019 primarily through national systems. Child Protection services benefited over 2633303 people through awareness programmes and 80000 children through psychosocial support. Enhanced capacities of the service providers have led to increasing access to child protection services for children at-risk. There has been a ministerial decree to scale up nationally the case management for services piloted in six governorates with MOSS. There are positive trends in favor of non-custodial alternatives to detention, including children in conflict with the law. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/12/2019
